text.tspan: Solution
Educating data science teams regarding the risks of trying
to use Jupyter Notebooks in production
Treat ML assets as first class citizens in DevOps processes
Providing mechanisms by which training sets, training scripts
and service wrappers may all be versioned appropriately
Providing mechanisms by which changes to training sets,
training scripts and service wrappers may all be auditable
across their full lifecycle
Treating training sets as managed assets under a MLOps
workflow
Managing the security of data in the MLOps process with
particular focus upon the increased risk associated with
aggregated data sets used for training or batch processing
Implications of privacy, GDPR and the right to be forgotten
upon training sets and deployed models
Methods for wrapping trained models as deployable services
in scenarios where data scientists training the models may not
be experienced software developers
Approaches for enabling all Machine Learning frameworks to
be used within the scope of MLOps, regardless of language or
platform
Approaches for enabling MLOps to support a broad range of
target platforms, including but not limited to CPU, GPU, TPU,
custom ASICs and neuromorphic silicon
Methods for ensuring efficient use of hardware in both training
and operational scenarios
Approaches for applying MLOps to very large scale problems
at petabyte scale and beyond
Providing appropriate pipeline tools to manage MLOps
workflows transparently as part of existing DevOps solutions
Testing ML assets appropriately
Governance processes for managing the release cycle of
MLOps assets, including Responsible AI principles

operational phases

Managing and tracking trade-offs
